# Walkthrough: Reliability & WhatsApp Alerts

I have completed the stabilization of the production build and implemented the requested WhatsApp alerting system to ensure 24/7 system health monitoring.

## 🚀 Build Stabilization

I addressed the Turbopack resolution errors that were blocking the deployment.

*   **Defensive Dynamic Imports:** Refactorerd [otel.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/observability/otel.ts) and [vitals-handler.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/observability/rum/vitals-handler.ts) to use `import()` only on the server/client appropriately, preventing "Module not found" errors during the build.
*   **Dependency Standardization:** Updated [package.json](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/package.json) to use a consistent set of OpenTelemetry versions, resolving internal link conflicts.
*   **External Packages:** Added `serverExternalPackages` to [next.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/next.config.ts) to properly handle heavy observability dependencies.

## 📱 WhatsApp Alerting System

A new dedicated service handles critical notifications directly to your phone.

*   **WhatsApp Service:** Created [whatsapp.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/whatsapp.ts), a utility that connects to Twilio to send high-priority alerts.
*   **Health Integration:** The [health API](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/app/api/health/route.ts) now triggers a WhatsApp message if the Database, Redis, or OpenAI connection fails.
*   **Anti-Spam Logic:** Implemented a 1-hour cooldown using Redis to ensure you only get one alert per failure event, avoiding message flooding.

## ✅ Verification Results

1.  **Build Check:** Ran static analysis verification; all "Can't resolve" errors related to `@opentelemetry` and `web-vitals` have been eliminated.
2.  **Alert Logic:** Verified that the health check correctly identifies failed services and attempts to trigger the [WhatsAppService](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/whatsapp.ts#7-73).
3.  **Cooldown Test:** Confirmed that Redis correctly stores the alert state to prevent duplicate notifications within the 1-hour window.

**Ready for the next deployment!** 🚀
